# Migrations

`YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_snake_case.sql`, strictly increasing. Every up migration in
`supabase/migrations/` must have a paired rollback in `supabase/rollback/` with
the same timestamp prefix. Apply rollbacks locally via `npm run db:rollback`.
Production rollbacks are a deliberate ops action. Changing an RPC signature:
drop (exact old sig) → create → re-grant.

## Realtime publication checklist

When a table needs client Realtime sync (**see `realtime-patterns.mdc`**):

1. RLS policies must exist before exposing the table.
2. Up migration: `alter publication supabase_realtime add table public.<table>;`
3. When RLS filters need the old row on UPDATE/DELETE:
   `alter table public.<table> replica identity full;`
4. Rollback: `alter publication supabase_realtime drop table if exists public.<table>;`
   (and revert replica identity if changed).
